I iterate all words and count a score for every word.
A word with biggest score becomes a candidate to call master.guess() (and it is deleted it from the next consideration).
To maintain the words score I use int array stats[6][26] (6 - character position, 26 - zero based character code).
For every guess > 0 I add it up to the current score at [pos][char] improving the finding of the next candidate
If guess returns 0 this means it is 100% that any other word with these [pos][char] is not the candidate. Marking it -1, again improving the next candidate.

```
/**
 * // This is the Master's API interface.
 * // You should not implement it, or speculate about its implementation
 * interface Master {
 *     public int guess(String word) {}
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    public void findSecretWord(String[] wordlist, Master master) {
        int[][] stats = new int[6][26];

        Set<String> words = new HashSet(Arrays.asList(wordlist));

        while(true){
            String nextWord = nextWord(stats, words);
            int matchCnt = master.guess(nextWord);
            if(matchCnt == 6)
                break;

            storeScore(stats, nextWord, matchCnt);
        }
