Idea:
For each point, if it is the peek point, we try to found the longest subsequence from its right and left;
The length of the array is **leftLIS[i]+rightLIS[i]-1**. 
We want to remove **n-(leftLIS[i]+rightLIS[i]-1)**

```
class Solution {
    public int minimumMountainRemovals(int[] A) {
        int res=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int n=A.length;
        int dp1[]=new int[n];
        int dp2[]=new int[n];

        dp1[0]=1;
        dp2[n-1]=1;

        for(int i=1;i<A.length;i++){
            int max=0;
            for(int j=i-1;j>=0;j--){
                if(A[j]<A[i]){
                    if(max<dp1[j]){
                        max=dp1[j];
                    }
                }
            }
            dp1[i]=max+1;
        }

        for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
            int max=0;
            for(int j=i+1;j<A.length;j++){
                if(A[j]<A[i]){
                    max=Math.max(max,dp2[j]);
                }
            }
            dp2[i]=max+1;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(dp1[i]<2||dp2[i]<2)continue;

            int len=dp1[i]+dp2[i]-1;
            res=Math.min(res,n-len);
        }


        return res;

    }
}
```

