/*
    Intuition 

    Step 1: Find LIS for each index from Left to Right and Right to Left
    Step 2: Find max Mountain by simply adding left and right LIS for any index and subtract 1
    because the current index element is added twice
    Step 3: Since, here we are interested in minimum number of elements to be removed
    subtract maxi from n => Minimum numbers to be removed

	This problem is actually Related to Bitonic Problem in which We can have 3 types of Mountain arrays:

Left Mount (Only Left Side Uphill and No Right side)
Right Mount (Only Right Side Uphill and No Left side)
Both Side
Here, in the problem statement they have asked about the mountain only which means the 3rd scenario and that is why to exclude the 1st and 2nd case we have put that condition.

Check this example:
[9,8,1,7,6,5,4,3,2,1]

dp1 dp2
1 9
1 8
1 1
2 7 (Max Mount for this problem statement)
2 6
2 5
2 4
2 3
2 2
1 1

Here, if we consider all three scenarios then our answer will be 1
But for this problem statement out answer will be 2
