# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The solution is based on LIS problem. We try to find LIS from 0 to index for left side and n-1 to index for right side.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumMountainRemovals(int[] a) {
        int n = a.length;
        int ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int i=1; i<n-1; i++) {
            int left = delByLeft(i-1, a[i], a);
            int right = delByRight(i+1, a[i], a);
            if(left==i || right==n-i-1) continue;
            ans = Math.min(ans, left + right);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public int binarySearch(int ele, List<Integer> a) {
        int l = 0, r = a.size()-1;
        int idx = -1;
        while (l<=r) {
            int mid = l + (r-l)/2;
            if(a.get(mid)>=ele) {
                idx = mid;
                r = mid - 1;
            } else {
                l = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        return idx;
    }
    public int delByLeft(int j, int ele, int[] a) {
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0; i<=j; i++) {
            if(a[i]>=ele) continue;

            if(ans.size()==0) {
                ans.add(a[i]);
            } else if(ans.get(ans.size()-1)<a[i]) {
                ans.add(a[i]);
            } else {
                int idx = binarySearch(a[i], ans);
                if(idx!=-1) {
                    ans.set(idx, a[i]);
                }
            }
        }
        return j - ans.size() + 1;
    }

    public int delByRight(int j, int ele, int[] a) {
        int n = a.length;
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=n-1; i>=j; i--) {
            if(a[i]>=ele) continue;

            if(ans.size()==0) {
                ans.add(a[i]);
            } else if(ans.get(ans.size()-1)<a[i]) {
                ans.add(a[i]);
            } else {
                int idx = binarySearch(a[i], ans);
                if(idx!=-1) {
                    ans.set(idx, a[i]);
                }
            }
        }
        return n - j - ans.size();
    }
}
```

